              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>For low-competition keywords, yes. Long-tail queries with 50–500 monthly searches are often winnable with strong on-page optimisation alone. Highly competitive terms (10,000+ monthly searches) also require off-page authority and backlinks.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">How do I check my on-page SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Google Search Console (free) shows ranking keywords and indexing issues. Ahrefs Site Audit, Semrush On-Page SEO Checker, and Screaming Frog crawl your site and flag title tag issues, missing H1s, broken internal links, and thin content.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between on-page SEO and technical SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>On-page SEO covers page-level factors you control directly: content quality, title tags, headings, internal links. Technical SEO covers server infrastructure: crawlability, site speed, structured data, and indexing configuration. Both are required — technical SEO ensures Google can access your pages; on-page SEO determines how they rank.</p></div></div>
